abstract: With a recent Emmy nod and a guest appearance from Jerry Seinfeld, NBC’s “30 Rock” earned a minor boost to its ratings Thursday. According to Nielsen’s estimates, the show’s season premiere drew 7.4 million viewers and a third-place finish in its 8:30 p.m. timeslot among adults 18 to 49.

headline.main: Ratings: A Boost from Seinfeld (Not That There’s Anything Wrong With That)
